      <p>
        <a href='/word_detail.php?id=398' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'yǒu', 'is / are / to have')" 
        onmouseout='hideToolTip()'>有</a> sentences use the verb <a href='/word_detail.php?id=398' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'yǒu', 'is / are / to have')" 
        onmouseout='hideToolTip()'>有</a> as the predicate.
        The basic form is: subject + <a href='/word_detail.php?id=398' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'yǒu', 'is / are / to have')" 
        onmouseout='hideToolTip()'>有</a> + object.
        For example,
      </p>
