        onmouseout="hideToolTip()">是</a>：
      </p>
      <p>
        A pivotal sentence has two predicates, the first of which has an object that serves as the subject for the second predicate.
        This object is called the pivot.
        The basic form of the pivotal sentence is:
      </p>
      <p>
        <a href='/word_detail.php?id=9249' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, '主語 zhǔyǔ', 'subject')" onmouseout="hideToolTip()">主语</a> ＋ <a href='/word_detail.php?id=9250' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, '謂語 wèiyǔ', 'predicate')" onmouseout="hideToolTip()">谓语</a>1（<a href='/word_detail.php?id=9256' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, '動詞 dòngcí', 'verb')" onmouseout="hideToolTip()">动词</a>） ＋ <a href='/word_detail.php?id=20815' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, '兼語 jiānyǔ', 'a pivot')" onmouseout="hideToolTip()">兼语</a> ＋ <a href='/word_detail.php?id=9250' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, '謂語 wèiyǔ', 'predicate')" 
        onmouseout="hideToolTip()">谓语</a>2
      </p>
      <p>
        Subject + predicate 1 (verb) + pivot + predicate 2
      </p>
      <p>
        <a href='/word_detail.php?id=2846' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'bǐrú', 'for example / for instance / such as')" 
        onmouseout="hideToolTip()">比如</a>：
